<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - INSTALL - LOWER SHIFT TOWER ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="11">
        <title>LOWER SHIFT TOWER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the three poppet balls and springs into the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022l4">Figure 214</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022l4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022l4" filename="../figg13/G13022l4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 214. Three Poppet Balls &#38; Springs</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The spring with the least tension must be placed in the over drive shift rail poppet hole to help
                    provide proper shifting.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the interlock and interlock plate (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022l5">Figure 215</hotlnk>). Tighten the bolts to 52 to 62 ft-lbs. (71 to 84 N&#183;
                m). The forward shift control position is shown here.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022l5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022l5" filename="../figg13/G13022l5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 215. Interlock &#38; Interlock Plate Installation</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The center shift control and remote shift control position is shown here (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022l6">Figure 216</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022l6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022l6" filename="../figg13/G13022l6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 216. Center Shift Control</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the pin and neutral safety switch if the unit is equipped with one (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022l7">Figure 217</hotlnk>). If not, make sure the plug is in place.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022l7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022l7" filename="../figg13/G13022l7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 217. Neutral Safety Switch</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the automatic shift rail poppet ball, spring, and poppet insert (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022l8">Figure 218</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022l8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022l8" filename="../figg13/G13022l8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 218. Automatic Shift Rail Poppet Ball</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the backup light pin and switch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022l9">Figure 219</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022l9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022l9" filename="../figg13/G13022l9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 219. Backup Light Pin &#38; Switch</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Shift all forks into neutral, then install the three air control valve pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022m0">Figure 220</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022m0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022m0" filename="../figg13/G13022m0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 220. Install Three Air Control Valve Pins</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the gasket and air control valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022m1">Figure 221</hotlnk>). Tighten the retaining bolts to 52 to 62 ft-lbs. (71 to
                84 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022m1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022m1" filename="../figg13/G13022m1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 221. Gasket &#38; Air Control Valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bench shift the transmission to make sure it is working properly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022m2">Figure 222</hotlnk>). Install the transmission into the vehicle. Refill the
                unit with fluid.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022m2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022m2" filename="../figg13/G13022m2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 222. Bench Shift Transmission</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the gasket and lower shift tower assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022m3">Figure 223</hotlnk>). The tower shift fingers must align with the overdrive
                and automatic shift rail detents. Secure the tower with bolts tightened to 52 to 62 ft-lbs. (71 to 84 N&#183;
                m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022m3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022m3" filename="../figg13/G13022m3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 223. Gasket &#38; Lower Shift Tower Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not apply sealant to the shift tower. It could prevent proper interlock functioning.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the upper shift tower (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022m4">Figure 224</hotlnk>). Tighten to 52 to 62 ft-lbs. (71 to 84 N&#183; ). Refer
                to,
                <hotlnk document="s13022x_53.xml" xrefid="g13022m9">AIR LINE PIPING</hotlnk>
                , when re-installing air lines.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022m4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022m4" filename="../figg13/G13022m4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 224. Install Upper Shift Tower</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Cut lines squarely to ensure a proper connection. Always use a razor-sharp edge to cut tubing.
                    Never use side cuts.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
